    "created_at": "2016-11-04T15:06:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-11-04T15:11:55Z",
    "body": "If you want to keep the `window` option (because you want the dialog to be shown as a sheet on macOS) you will have to use this workaround:\n\n``` js\ndialog.showMessageBox(window, options, function(response) {\n  if (response == 0) {\n     setTimeout(() => autoUpdater.quitAndInstall(), 1);\n  }\n}); \n```\n\n...or use the sync version of dialog:\n\n``` js\nconst response = dialog.showMessageBox(window, options);\n\nif (response == 0) {\n  autoUpdater.quitAndInstall();\n}\n```\n"
  },
